Young people in our society today are struggling with substance abuse. Different organizations have come up with different schemes to help cope with the issue of drug addiction among the youth. Today, fans across the world are celebrating Mac Miller's birthday. Miller died in 2018 after overdosing on fentanyl, a potent painkiller said to be 50 times more potent than heroin. His death was ruled an accidental overdose, from a combination of fentanyl, alcohol and cocaine. Vince staples, one of Miller’s friends, announced the launch of the Mac Miller legacy fund which will help in aiding young upcoming musicians who are struggling with substance abuse. On the organization’s webpage, they will receive a $50,000 grant from the Miller’s circle of funds started my Mac Miller’s family after his untimely passing from drug overdose back in September 7, 2018. The funds are supposed to help young artists from 27 years and under who are struggling with drug addiction. Fans, worldwide, today took to twitter to express their feelings and on how Miller impacted their lives with both his music and willingness to help the young upcoming generation. The hip-hop artist's act of kindness and good heart is even evident in one of Ariana Grande’s song, who was Miller's ex-girlfriend, “thank you, next” where she says “wish I could say thank you to Malcom, ‘coz he was an angel.” Happy birthday to the late Mac Miller.